\section{Generating spreadsheets for HR}

This module produces two kinds of Excel workbook for the administrative
process around teaching assistants.  A \emph{time report}
(\foreignlanguage{swedish}{tidrapport}) accounts for hours already worked and
is what the course responsible signs and sends to HR for payment.  A
\emph{planning sheet} (\foreignlanguage{swedish}{planering}) is filled in
\emph{before} an amanuensis employment to decide its percentage of full time.

The two share a toolkit ([[openpyxl]] and [[PIL]]) but differ on the
one axis that shapes the code: the time report is \emph{built from an empty
workbook}, because we own every number in it; the planning sheet is produced by
\emph{filling a department-provided template}, because that template carries
formulas the department trusts.  We must therefore touch only the input cells
and leave the formulas untouched, so that the sheet recomputes exactly the
totals our own functions produce.

